{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":609,"text":"(Singing) I see the moon.\nThe moon sees me."},{"time":6296,"text":"The moon sees somebody that I don't see."},{"time":12708,"text":"God bless the moon, and God bless me."},{"time":19243,"text":"And God bless the somebody\nthat I don't see."},{"time":25673,"text":"If I get to heaven, before you do,"},{"time":31987,"text":"I'll make a hole and pull you through."},{"time":38083,"text":"And I'll write your name on every star,"},{"time":44062,"text":"and that way the world"},{"time":47356,"text":"won't seem so far."}]},{"cues":[{"time":51079,"text":"The astronaut will not be at work today."},{"time":55111,"text":"He has called in sick."},{"time":56791,"text":"He has turned off his cell phone,\nhis laptop, his pager, his alarm clock."},{"time":61943,"text":"There is a fat yellow cat\nasleep on his couch,"},{"time":65116,"text":"raindrops against the window"},{"time":66884,"text":"and not even the hint\nof coffee in the kitchen air."},{"time":70623,"text":"Everybody is in a tizzy."},{"time":71896,"text":"The engineers on the 15th floor have\nstopped working on their particle machine."},{"time":75866,"text":"The anti-gravity room is leaking,"},{"time":77668,"text":"and even the freckled kid with glasses,"},{"time":79572,"text":"whose only job is to take\nout the trash, is nervous,"},{"time":82270,"text":"fumbles the bag, spills\na banana peel and a paper cup."},{"time":85003,"text":"Nobody notices."},{"time":86449,"text":"They are too busy recalculating\nwhat this all mean for lost time."},{"time":89898,"text":"How many galaxies\nare we losing per second?"},{"time":91954,"text":"How long before next rocket\ncan be launched?"},{"time":94028,"text":"Somewhere an electron\nflies off its energy cloud."},{"time":96923,"text":"A black hole has erupted."},{"time":98913,"text":"A mother finishes setting\nthe table for dinner."},{"time":101238,"text":"A Law &amp; Order marathon is starting."},{"time":103323,"text":"The astronaut is asleep."},{"time":105568,"text":"He has forgotten to turn off his watch,"},{"time":107495,"text":"which ticks, like a metal\npulse against his wrist."},{"time":110270,"text":"He does not hear it."},{"time":111869,"text":"He dreams of coral reefs and plankton."},{"time":114942,"text":"His fingers find\nthe pillowcase's sailing masts."},{"time":118105,"text":"He turns on his side,\nopens his eyes at once."},{"time":121197,"text":"He thinks that scuba divers must have\nthe most wonderful job in the world."},{"time":125951,"text":"So much water to glide through!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":131070,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":136322,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":138127,"text":"When I was little, I could\nnot understand the concept"},{"time":142996,"text":"that you could only live one life."},{"time":145560,"text":"I don't mean this metaphorically."},{"time":147164,"text":"I mean, I literally thought\nthat I was going to get to do"},{"time":150433,"text":"everything there was to do"},{"time":152503,"text":"and be everything there was to be."},{"time":155123,"text":"It was only a matter of time."},{"time":156899,"text":"And there was no limitation\nbased on age or gender"},{"time":159947,"text":"or race or even appropriate time period."},{"time":163058,"text":"I was sure that I was going\nto actually experience"},{"time":166533,"text":"what it felt like to be a leader\nof the civil rights movement"},{"time":170351,"text":"or a ten-year old boy living\non a farm during the dust bowl"},{"time":174009,"text":"or an emperor of the Tang\ndynasty in China."},{"time":177651,"text":"My mom says that when people asked me"},{"time":179676,"text":"what I wanted to be when I grew up,\nmy typical response was:"},{"time":183279,"text":"princess-ballerina-astronaut."},{"time":185458,"text":"And what she doesn't understand\nis that I wasn't trying to invent"},{"time":188627,"text":"some combined super profession."},{"time":190634,"text":"I was listing things I thought\nI was gonna get to be:"},{"time":194035,"text":"a princess and a ballerina\nand an astronaut."},{"time":197120,"text":"and I'm pretty sure the list\nprobably went on from there."},{"time":199883,"text":"I usually just got cut off."},{"time":201905,"text":"It was never a question\nof if I was gonna get to do something"},{"time":204795,"text":"so much of a question of when."}]},{"cues":[{"time":207278,"text":"And I was sure that if I was going\nto do everything,"},{"time":209779,"text":"that it probably meant I had\nto move pretty quickly,"},{"time":212239,"text":"because there was a lot\nof stuff I needed to do."},{"time":214509,"text":"So my life was constantly\nin a state of rushing."},{"time":216803,"text":"I was always scared\nthat I was falling behind."},{"time":218994,"text":"And since I grew up\nin New York City, as far as I could tell,"},{"time":222398,"text":"rushing was pretty normal."},{"time":225128,"text":"But, as I grew up, I had\nthis sinking realization,"},{"time":229108,"text":"that I wasn't gonna get to live\nany more than one life."},{"time":233422,"text":"I only knew what it felt like\nto be a teenage girl"},{"time":236452,"text":"in New York City,"},{"time":237627,"text":"not a teenage boy in New Zealand,"},{"time":239942,"text":"not a prom queen in Kansas."},{"time":243043,"text":"I only got to see through my lens."},{"time":244988,"text":"And it was around this time\nthat I became obsessed with stories,"},{"time":248320,"text":"because it was through stories\nthat I was able to see"},{"time":251471,"text":"through someone else's lens,\nhowever briefly or imperfectly."},{"time":255589,"text":"And I started craving hearing\nother people's experiences"},{"time":258725,"text":"because I was so jealous\nthat there were entire lives"},{"time":262312,"text":"that I was never gonna get to live,"},{"time":264027,"text":"and I wanted to hear\nabout everything that I was missing."},{"time":266726,"text":"And by transitive property,"},{"time":268044,"text":"I realized that some people\nwere never gonna get to experience"},{"time":271297,"text":"what it felt like to be a teenage girl\nin New York city."},{"time":274005,"text":"Which meant that they weren't gonna know"},{"time":275934,"text":"what the subway ride\nafter your first kiss feels like,"},{"time":279180,"text":"or how quiet it gets when its snows."},{"time":282022,"text":"And I wanted them to know,\nI wanted to tell them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":284658,"text":"And this became the focus of my obsession."},{"time":287109,"text":"I busied myself telling stories\nand sharing stories and collecting them."},{"time":290758,"text":"And it's not until recently"},{"time":292766,"text":"that I realized that\nI can't always rush poetry."},{"time":297666,"text":"In April for National Poetry Month,\nthere's this challenge"},{"time":301028,"text":"that many poets in the poetry\ncommunity participate in,"},{"time":304170,"text":"and its called the 30/30 Challenge."},{"time":306551,"text":"The idea is you write a new poem"},{"time":309297,"text":"every single day\nfor the entire month of April."},{"time":312916,"text":"And last year, I tried it\nfor the first time"},{"time":314996,"text":"and was thrilled by the efficiency\nat which I was able to produce poetry."},{"time":319765,"text":"But at the end of the month, I looked\nback at these 30 poems I had written"},{"time":323399,"text":"and discovered that they were\nall trying to tell the same story,"},{"time":327442,"text":"it had just taken me 30 tries to figure\nout the way that it wanted to be told."},{"time":332275,"text":"And I realized that this is probably true\nof other stories on an even larger scale."},{"time":336220,"text":"I have stories that I have\ntried to tell for years,"},{"time":338672,"text":"rewriting and rewriting and constantly\nsearching for the right words."}]},{"cues":[{"time":343084,"text":"There's a French poet and essayist\nby the name of Paul Val√©ry"},{"time":346393,"text":"who said a poem is never\nfinished, it is only abandoned."},{"time":350178,"text":"And this terrifies me"},{"time":351353,"text":"because it implies that I could keep\nre-editing and rewriting forever"},{"time":354756,"text":"and its up to me to decide\nwhen a poem is finished"},{"time":358233,"text":"and when I can walk away from it."},{"time":360978,"text":"And this goes directly against\nmy very obsessive nature"},{"time":363709,"text":"to try to find the right answer\nand the perfect words and the right form."},{"time":367352,"text":"And I use poetry in my life,"},{"time":369457,"text":"as a way to help me navigate\nand work through things."},{"time":372193,"text":"But just because I end the poem,\ndoesn't mean that I've solved"},{"time":375423,"text":"what it was I was puzzling through."},{"time":378001,"text":"I like to revisit old poetry"},{"time":379859,"text":"because it shows me exactly\nwhere I was at that moment"},{"time":383698,"text":"and what it was I was trying to navigate"},{"time":385635,"text":"and the words that I chose to help me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":388468,"text":"Now, I have a story"},{"time":389845,"text":"that I've been stumbling\nover for years and years"},{"time":392718,"text":"and I'm not sure if I've found\nthe prefect form,"},{"time":395392,"text":"or whether this is just one attempt"},{"time":397408,"text":"and I will try to rewrite it later\nin search of a better way to tell it."},{"time":401177,"text":"But I do know that later, when I look back"},{"time":404201,"text":"I will be able to know that\nthis is where I was at this moment"},{"time":408224,"text":"and this is what I was trying to navigate,"},{"time":410447,"text":"with these words, here,\nin this room, with you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":416105,"text":"So --"},{"time":418652,"text":"Smile."}]},{"cues":[{"time":425310,"text":"It didn't always work this way."},{"time":427874,"text":"There's a time you had\nto get your hands dirty."},{"time":430305,"text":"When you were in the dark,\nfor most of it, fumbling was a given."},{"time":434416,"text":"If you needed more\ncontrast, more saturation,"},{"time":437836,"text":"darker darks and brighter brights,"},{"time":439963,"text":"they called it extended development."},{"time":442684,"text":"It meant you spent longer inhaling\nchemicals, longer up to your wrist."},{"time":446010,"text":"It wasn't always easy."},{"time":447937,"text":"Grandpa Stewart was a Navy photographer."},{"time":450731,"text":"Young, red-faced\nwith his sleeves rolled up,"},{"time":453699,"text":"fists of fingers like fat rolls of coins,"},{"time":456351,"text":"he looked like Popeye\nthe sailor man come to life."},{"time":459195,"text":"Crooked smile, tuft of chest hair,"},{"time":461636,"text":"he showed up to World War II,\nwith a smirk and a hobby."},{"time":465041,"text":"When they asked him if he knew\nmuch about photography,"},{"time":467731,"text":"he lied, learned to read\nEurope like a map,"},{"time":471043,"text":"upside down, from the height\nof a fighter plane,"},{"time":474257,"text":"camera snapping, eyelids flapping"},{"time":476782,"text":"the darkest darks and brightest brights."},{"time":479021,"text":"He learned war like he could\nread his way home."}]},{"cues":[{"time":482520,"text":"When other men returned,\nthey would put their weapons out to rest,"},{"time":485648,"text":"but he brought the lenses\nand the cameras home with him."},{"time":488299,"text":"Opened a shop, turned it\ninto a family affair."},{"time":491386,"text":"My father was born into this\nworld of black and white."},{"time":494830,"text":"His basketball hands learned\nthe tiny clicks and slides"},{"time":498024,"text":"of lens into frame, film into camera,"},{"time":500619,"text":"chemical into plastic bin."},{"time":502120,"text":"His father knew the equipment\nbut not the art."},{"time":505308,"text":"He knew the darks but not the brights."},{"time":507175,"text":"My father learned the magic,\nspent his time following light."},{"time":510874,"text":"Once he traveled across the country\nto follow a forest fire,"},{"time":514532,"text":"hunted it with his camera for a week."},{"time":517929,"text":"\"Follow the light,\" he said."},{"time":519698,"text":"\"Follow the light.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":520898,"text":"There are parts of me\nI only recognize from photographs."},{"time":524095,"text":"The loft on Wooster Street\nwith the creaky hallways,"},{"time":526825,"text":"the twelve-foot ceilings,\nwhite walls and cold floors."},{"time":529549,"text":"This was my mother's home,\nbefore she was mother."},{"time":532372,"text":"Before she was wife, she was artist."},{"time":535253,"text":"And the only two rooms in the house,"},{"time":537016,"text":"with walls that reached\nall the way up to the ceiling,"},{"time":539571,"text":"and doors that opened and closed,"},{"time":541182,"text":"were the bathroom and the darkroom."},{"time":543814,"text":"The darkroom she built herself,"},{"time":545917,"text":"with custom-made stainless steel sinks,\nan 8x10 bed enlarger"},{"time":550536,"text":"that moved up and down\nby a giant hand crank,"},{"time":552972,"text":"a bank of color-balanced lights,"},{"time":554679,"text":"a white glass wall for viewing prints,"},{"time":556668,"text":"a drying rack that moved\nin and out from the wall."},{"time":559034,"text":"My mother built herself a darkroom."},{"time":561144,"text":"Made it her home."},{"time":562431,"text":"Fell in love with a man\nwith basketball hands,"},{"time":565115,"text":"with the way he looked at light."}]},{"cues":[{"time":567375,"text":"They got married. Had a baby."},{"time":569482,"text":"Moved to a house near a park."},{"time":571696,"text":"But they kept the loft on Wooster Street"},{"time":573633,"text":"for birthday parties and treasure hunts."},{"time":576206,"text":"The baby tipped the grayscale,"},{"time":578634,"text":"filled her parents' photo albums\nwith red balloons and yellow icing."},{"time":582293,"text":"The baby grew into a girl\nwithout freckles,"},{"time":585086,"text":"with a crooked smile,"},{"time":586602,"text":"who didn‚Äôt understand why her friends\ndid not have darkrooms in their houses,"},{"time":591086,"text":"who never saw her parents kiss,"},{"time":593022,"text":"who never saw them hold hands."}]},{"cues":[{"time":595006,"text":"But one day, another baby showed up."},{"time":596768,"text":"This one with perfect straight\nhair and bubble gum cheeks."},{"time":599975,"text":"They named him sweet potato."},{"time":601625,"text":"When he laughed, he laughed so loudly"},{"time":603581,"text":"he scared the pigeons on the fire escape"},{"time":605763,"text":"And the four of them lived\nin that house near the park."},{"time":608763,"text":"The girl with no freckles,\nthe sweet potato boy,"},{"time":611342,"text":"the basketball father and darkroom mother"},{"time":613492,"text":"and they lit their candles\nand said their prayers,"},{"time":616144,"text":"and the corners of the photographs curled."}]},{"cues":[{"time":618959,"text":"One day, some towers fell."},{"time":621491,"text":"And the house near the park\nbecame a house under ash, so they escaped"},{"time":625244,"text":"in backpacks, on bicycles to darkrooms"},{"time":628531,"text":"But the loft of Wooster Street\nwas built for an artist,"},{"time":631384,"text":"not a family of pigeons,"},{"time":634162,"text":"and walls that do not reach the ceiling\ndo not hold in the yelling"},{"time":637558,"text":"and the man with basketball hands\nput his weapons out to rest."},{"time":641824,"text":"He could not fight this war,\nand no maps pointed home."},{"time":645442,"text":"His hands no longer fit his camera,"},{"time":647665,"text":"no longer fit his wife's,"},{"time":649276,"text":"no longer fit his body."},{"time":651299,"text":"The sweet potato boy mashed\nhis fists into his mouth"},{"time":654007,"text":"until he had nothing more to say."}]},{"cues":[{"time":655604,"text":"So, the girl without freckles\nwent treasure hunting on her own."},{"time":659497,"text":"And on Wooster Street, in a building\nwith the creaky hallways"},{"time":662932,"text":"and the loft with the 12-foot ceilings"},{"time":664784,"text":"and the darkroom with too many sinks"},{"time":666776,"text":"under the color-balanced lights,\nshe found a note,"},{"time":669322,"text":"tacked to the wall with a thumb-tack,\nleft over from a time before towers,"},{"time":673933,"text":"from the time before babies."},{"time":676588,"text":"And the note said: \"A guy sure loves\nthe girl who works in the darkroom.\""},{"time":682758,"text":"It was a year before my father\npicked up a camera again."},{"time":686238,"text":"His first time out, he followed\nthe Christmas lights,"},{"time":688800,"text":"dotting their way through\nNew York City's trees,"},{"time":691307,"text":"tiny dots of light, blinking out at him\nfrom out of the darkest darks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":696030,"text":"A year later he traveled\nacross the country to follow a forest fire"},{"time":699952,"text":"stayed for a week hunting\nit with his camera,"},{"time":702488,"text":"it was ravaging the West Coast"},{"time":704364,"text":"eating 18-wheeler trucks in its stride."},{"time":706618,"text":"On the other side of the country,"},{"time":708221,"text":"I went to class and wrote a poem\nin the margins of my notebook."},{"time":711603,"text":"We have both learned the art of capture."},{"time":714059,"text":"Maybe we are learning\nthe art of embracing."},{"time":716936,"text":"Maybe we are learning\nthe art of letting go."}]},{"cues":[{"time":721357,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}